<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> Not really going to go into the actions of the guild in this thread, because I dont know what transpired... This is more of a reply to the Aary Rule in general, and a bit of history.<br>
<br>
Not every guild on Drinal has followed the &quot;Aary rule&quot; including one of the older, respected guilds on Drinal. This guild would be the Femax, Maxwells, Blue Gale (Yes I'm aware that IB now is part of  this raiding force, however at the time they were not) alliance, (now lovingly refered to as Voltron) When WL/CT was doing NToV, our main competition was FeMax, and they stated they would regard NToV as FFA. <br>
<br>
I dont know the full reason why  FeMax didnt want to follow the rule, but in all honesty it worked out just fine, and there was no bad blood formed as a result us Killing Aary, and Femax getting some of the NToV dragons, or Vice versa. (In all honesty it worked out better for us, as they could beat us to most spawns, due to their timezone)<br>
<br>
If a guild states that they dont want to follow the Aaryonar rule, I honestly believe that is their choice. However since the rule is generally assumed to be followed, communication of the guild that choose's to go down that road should alert other guilds that raid NToV of their intent, and posistion on the rule...<br>
<br>
The Aary rule in itself is biased imo. Is it &quot;fair&quot; that because after a server goes that guild that raids near that time has little to no competition to race to  the spawn (While admitadly patches are a pain in the ass for them sometimes, as it usually eats up some of their evening/prime playtime) Could get NToV rights nearly every patch, simply due to the fact of the time they are raiding?<br>
